'''Nigma Galaxy''' is a UAE-based Esports organization. Spread across a diverse international roster of 10 teams the organization has professionals from 22 countries. Since its introduction to the competitive gaming scene in 2019, the team has fielded lineups in titles such as [https://liquipedia.net/counterstrike/Galaxy_Racer/ CS: GO], League of Legends, [https://liquipedia.net/dota2/Galaxy_Racer/ Dota 2], [https://liquipedia.net/dota2/Galaxy_Racer/ PUBG Mobile],  Call of Duty: Mobile, [https://liquipedia.net/dota2/Galaxy_Racer/ Rocket League], and Fortnite. On September 20th, 2021 '''Galaxy Racer''' merged with '''Team Nigma''' to create '''Nigma Galaxy'''.[https://twitter.com/NigmaGalaxy/status/1439861893934432259]

The organization entered the India scene in July 2020 by acquiring the roster of the previous PUBG Mobile team; [[Celtz]].

